  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the probability of winning a lotto?",
  "response": "The probability of winning a lottery depends on the specific rules of the lottery you are playing, such as the total number of possible combinations and the number of winning combinations.\n\nHere's a general way to calculate the probability:\n\n1. **Identify the total number of combinations**: This is typically calculated based on the total numbers available and how many numbers you need to choose. For example, in a 6/49 lottery, you must choose 6 numbers from a set of 49.\n\n   The total number of combinations in a 6/49 lottery is calculated using the combination formula: \n\n   \\[\n   C(n, k) = \\frac{n!}{k!(n-k)!}\n   \\]\n\n   Where:\n   - \\( n \\) is the total number of available numbers (49 in this case),\n   - \\( k \\) is the number of numbers to be chosen (6 in this case).\n\n   For a 6/49 lottery, the total combinations would be:\n\n   \\[\n   C(49, 6) = \\frac{49!}{6!(49-6)!} = \\frac{49!}{6! \\times 43!} = 13,983,816\n   \\]\n\n2. **Determine the number of winning outcomes**: Generally, in a standard lottery, there is only one winning combination.\n\n3. **Calculate the probability of winning**: To find the probability \\( P \\) of winning, you can use the formula:\n\n   \\[\n   P(\\text{winning}) = \\frac{\\text{Number of winning outcomes}}{\\text{Total number of combinations}} = \\frac{1}{13,983,816}\n   \\]\n\nIn this example, the probability of winning the jackpot in a 6/49 lottery is approximately \\( 1 \\) in \\( 13,983,816 \\), or about \\( 0.0000000715 \\) (or \\( 0.00000715\\% \\)).\n   \nKeep in mind that the odds will vary for different lottery formats, and some lotteries also offer smaller prizes for matching fewer numbers, which can affect your overall odds of winning anything at all.",
